account and group
command

solaris:
ex:
1. add user
ex:
useradd deeplove
ex:
useradd -d /Pool-1/UserHome/test -s /usr/bin/nassh -m test123
add user test123, with home dir /Pool-1/UserHome/test
-d: home dir path
-m: create home dir

2. add group
groupadd gn1

3. show user list
dispuid

4. show group list
dispgid

5. show id of user
id  test

6. change user's uid
usermod -u 10000 test

7. add user to group
ex:
useradd -G myGroup peter

8. show user info
ex:
id abc
->
uid=101(abc) gid=1(other)

9. modify user's group
ex:
usermod -g myGroup abc
    
10. delete group
ex:
groupdel myGroup

11. find group's users
ex:
getent group myg
->
myg::104:peter1,peter2

12. show users info
getent passwd

13. add user with specific uid
useradd -u 12000 peter


linux:
set password 
ex:
passwd deeplove
